Hunt 每日热榜 | 2026-01-22\",\"url\":\"https://m.toutiao.com/a7598113038247526964/\"}]\n\nBased on my search, I found several **AI coding tools that launched on Product Hunt in February 2026**. Here's a summary:\n\n## Top AI Coding Tools Launched in February 2026\n\n### 1. **Straion** (Late February 2026)\n- **Launch Date**: February 22, 2026\n- **Upvotes**: 349\n- **Description**: A centralized rules management platform for AI coding assistants like Claude Code, GitHub Copilot, and Cursor\n- **Key Features**: Automatically selects appropriate rules for each programming task to help deliver enterprise-grade code 10x faster\n\n### 2. **Inspector - \"Figma for Claude Code\"** (Early February 2026)\n- **Launch Date**: February 9, 2026\n- **Upvotes**: 462 (Featured)\n- **Description**: A visual editing tool that connects with AI assistants (Claude Code, Codex, Cursor)\n- **Key Features**: Lets you click UI elements, make visual adjustments, and automatically writes changes to your codebase - essentially eliminating design handoff\n\n### 3. **Claudebin** (Mid-February 2026)\n- **Launch Date**: February 20, 2026\n- **Upvotes**: 228 (Featured)\n- **Description**: A tool to export and share Claude Code sessions as restorable links\n- **Key Features**: Addresses the issue that Claude Code stores session data locally in non-human-readable format, making it easier to review or share useful refactoring and tool usage sessions\n\n### 4. **Happycapy** (Mid-February 2026)\n- **Launch Date**: February 12, 2026\n- **Upvotes**: 789 (Featured)\n- **Description**: Transforms your browser into a local computer powered by Claude Code\n- **Key Features**: User-friendly interface for everyday users to complete real work from programming and design to daily tasks - all powered by Claude Code\n\n### 5. **Axel** (Early February 2026)\n- **Launch Date**: February 9, 2026\n- **Upvotes**: 249 (Featured)\n- **Description**: An AI programming assistant and task management tool for macOS\n- **Key Features**: Native macOS application with keyboard operations, Claude integration, Codex support, and efficient workflow deployment\n\n## Additional Related Tools from February 2026:\n- **GitHub Agent HQ**: Use Claude, Codex, and Copilot directly in GitHub and VS Code (178 upvotes)\n- **blivz**: Open-source custom tools for modern GTM workflows with Claude Code integration\n\n---\n\n**Important Note**: The search results reference **February 2026**, which is in the future from our current perspective. These results appear to be from speculative/hypothetical content or possibly from sources that are presenting future-looking scenarios. The tools mentioned (like Claude Code) are real/current products, but the specific launch dates and Product Hunt details for February 2026 should be verified closer to that actual timeframe.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
